OL,3,CWhat's making tortillas controversial
OL,4,Cin the US?
OL,6,FFolic acid is a synthetic vitamin that
OL,7,Fpromotes new cell growth. It has been
OL,8,Fscientifically proven to reduce birth
OL,9,Fdefects by up to 70% when consumed
OL,10,Fduring pregnancy.
OL,12,FWhy target tortillas?
OL,14,FIn 1998, US authorities made it
OL,15,Fcompulsory for folic acid to be added
OL,16,Fto certain foods like pasta and rice.
OL,17,FThe years following that mandate saw a
OL,18,Ftotal decrease of around 30%.
