OL,6,FHowever, since that mandate, there has
OL,7,Fnot been as significant a decrease in
OL,8,FLatino babies being born with birth
OL,9,Fdefects US.
OL,11,FIn fact, in the US, Latino babies have
OL,12,Fthe highest prevalence of folic acid-
OL,13,Frelated birth defects compared to
OL,14,Fother ethnic groups.
OL,16,FCalifornia is now targeting tortillas
OL,17,Fas they are predominantly eaten by the
OL,18,FLatino population. Lawmakers say that
OL,19,Ftargeting foods that are staples in
OL,20,Fthese households is an important step
OL,21,Ftowards health equity.
