OL,6,FThe UK government has announced that
OL,7,Fit will require non-wholemeal wheat
OL,8,Fflour to be fortified with folic acid
OL,9,Fby the end of 2026.
OL,11,FThis will affect a range of products
OL,12,Fin the UK, including bread, cake, and
OL,13,Fpasta.
OL,15,FThe Department for Health and Social
OL,16,FCare has outlined that they hope that
OL,17,Fthis law will prevent around 200 cases
OL,18,Fof neural tube defects in babies every
OL,19,Fyear and improve overall health when
OL,20,Fpregnant.
